aspace_helpers.title: multiple boxes in non-dsc2 components migrated as nested containers

comments.body:
- [x] report out nested boxes from ASpace
- [x] report out sibling boxes with properties from migrated EADs / containers
- [x] match both reports on cid
- [x] delete subcontainers per ASpace report (written and tested)
- [ ] re-create deleted subcontainers as top_containers with properties from EAD, if they don't already exist
- [ ] report out uri's of newly minted containers (or capture uri's at creation if possible?)
- [ ] update ao's from ASpace report with uris

required fields for top_container:
```
top_container.container_profile
top_container.indicator
top_container.type
top_container.barcode
top_container.container_locations
container_location.status
container_location.start_date
container_location.ref
```

```
{
  "barcode"=>"12345567890",
  "indicator"=>"1",
  "type"=>"box",
  "ils_holding_id"=>"TEST01_f1",
  "container_locations"=>[{
    "status"=>"current",
    "start_date"=>"2020-11-10",
    "note"=>"this is a test",
    "ref"=>"/locations/23647"}
  ],
  "container_profile"=>{"ref"=>"/container_profiles/3"}
  }
```

Some of the improperly nested containers already exist, because they were the first containers in other components. 

To check that the containers to be created don't yet exist:
--get all containers for the repo
--for each nid, check whether a container with that barcode already exists
